   <taskbody>
      <prereq class="- topic/section task/prereq ">
         <ul class="- topic/ul ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">The document file type is an allowed file type as configured in the application. <ph product="Exclude_PG_Content" class="- topic/ph ">For information on allowed file types, refer to <xref href="../../Administration/System_Configurations/App_Settings.dita"
                        class="- topic/xref ">Application Settings</xref>.</ph>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">A document of the same name does not exist in the folder.</p>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </prereq>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Documents</uicontrol> module, you can upload various file types as configured in the application. You can upload documents of any file types such as Microsoft files, PDFs, images, audios, videos, and other file types.</p>
         <p product="Forge_Viewer" class="- topic/p ">You can also upload 2-Dimensional (2D), 3-Dimensional (3D), and other format drawing files that are created using AutoCAD and other designing software.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">While viewing a document,<ph product="Forge_Viewer" class="- topic/ph "> based on the file type,</ph>
            <ph conref="../../../Warehouse/Product_Name_Warehouse.dita#reference-9043/product_name"
                class="- topic/ph "/> enables various functionalities.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">You can also add metadata information to documents uploaded to the application. You can associate a workflow to a document to obtain approvals from stakeholders. </p>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step conref="../../../Warehouse/Task_Warehouse/AcsPrjContDocsNav.dita#task-5739/AccProContDocFolder"
               class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "/>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">New</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">NEW DOCUMENT</uicontrol> page is displayed.</info>
            <info product="PG_Screenshot" class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <title class="- topic/title ">New Document</title>
                  <image href="../../CoSP/Document_Management/Screenshot/New_Document.jpg"
                         class="- topic/image "
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </info>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <note class="- topic/note "> You can configure the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">NEW DOCUMENT </uicontrol>page to record additional attributes of the document by selecting an appropriate document property template for the project during project creation. Document property templates are defined in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Document Properties </uicontrol>catalog of the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Library </uicontrol>module. <ph product="Exclude_PG_Content" class="- topic/ph ">For more information on configuring the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">New Document </uicontrol>page, refer to <xref href="../../Library_Management/Standard_Library_Catalogs/Document_Management/DocProps.dita"
                           class="- topic/xref ">Document Properties</xref>.</ph>
               </note>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Provide the appropriate information in the fields, as described in the following table.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <table colsep="1" rowsep="1" class="- topic/table ">
                  <tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup ">
                     <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="30%" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                     <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="70%" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                     <thead class="- topic/thead ">
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">Field Name</entry>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">Description</entry>
                        </row>
                     </thead>
                     <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">Title</entry>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">Enter the document name.<note class="- topic/note ">If you do not enter the title,  the name of the file is updated in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Title</uicontrol> box. </note>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">New Document</entry>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">To upload documents,  drag and drop the appropriate files into the  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">New Document</uicontrol> box.<p class="- topic/p ">Alternatively, perform the following steps:<ol class="- topic/ol ">
                                    <li class="- topic/li ">
                                       <p class="- topic/p ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Select files</uicontrol>.</p>
                                       <p class="- topic/p ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Open</uicontrol> dialog box is displayed.</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li class="- topic/li ">
                                       <p class="- topic/p ">Click the required document to upload.</p>
                                       <p class="- topic/p ">Alternatively, to select multiple files to upload, press CTRL, and then click the required documents. </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li class="- topic/li ">
                                       <p class="- topic/p ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Open</uicontrol>.</p>
                                       <p class="- topic/p ">The selected files are displayed.</p>
                                    </li>
                                 </ol>
                              </p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">Template Document</entry>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">To use the document as a template document for the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Mail Merge</uicontrol> feature, select the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Template Document </uicontrol> check box. <ph product="Exclude_PG_Content" class="- topic/ph ">For information on Mail Merge, refer to <xref href="../../Common_Application_Features/Mail_Merge/MailMerge.dita"
                                       class="- topic/xref ">Mail Merge</xref>.</ph>
                              <note class="- topic/note ">Only files of Word format are used as templates for the Mail Merge feature. </note>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">Workflow</entry>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">Select the appropriate workflow to receive approvals from the stakeholder. Available options are workflows defined for the document management module. <p product="Exclude_PG_Content" class="- topic/p ">For information on workflows, refer to <xref href="../../Administration/Configuration_Toolkit/Workflow_Management/WFMgmt.dita"
                                       class="- topic/xref ">Workflow Management</xref>.</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">PWA Project Number</entry>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">The identification code of the associated project.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">Project Name</entry>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">The name of the associated project.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">Document Type</entry>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">Select the document type of the files being uploaded.</entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Save</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The list page of the folder is displayed. <p product="Forge_Viewer" class="- topic/p ">In the list page, the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">File View Status</uicontrol> column displays the current status of the document being uploaded. Each status is associated with a color. You can view the uploaded document only when the status is <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Ready</uicontrol>.<note class="- topic/note "> If the drawing file viewer is not configured, then the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">File View Status</uicontrol> column is not displayed in the list page.</note>The following are the different statuses:<table colsep="1" rowsep="1" class="- topic/table ">
                     <tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup ">
                        <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                        <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                        <colspec colname="c3" colnum="3" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                        <thead class="- topic/thead ">
                           <row class="- topic/row ">
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Status</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Icon Color</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Description</entry>
                           </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                           <row class="- topic/row ">
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Processing</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                 <image href="../../Icons/BlueStatus.png"
                                        class="- topic/image "
                                        placement="inline">
                                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Translation in progress</alt>
                                 </image>Blue</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry "> Translation in progress</entry>
                           </row>
                           <row class="- topic/row ">
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Failed</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                 <image href="../../Icons/FV-RedCrcl.png"
                                        class="- topic/image "
                                        placement="inline">
                                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">Translation failed</alt>
                                 </image>Red</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry "> Translation failed</entry>
                           </row>
                           <row class="- topic/row ">
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Ready</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                 <image width="1cm"
                                        href="../../Icons/FV-GreenCrcl.png"
                                        class="- topic/image "
                                        placement="inline">
                                    <alt class="- topic/alt ">File is ready to view</alt>
                                 </image>Green</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">File is ready to view</entry>
                           </row>
                        </tbody>
                     </tgroup>
                  </table>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
      </steps>
